SÃ©rgio T. Rebelo (born October 29, 1959) is a Portuguese economist who is the current Tokai Bank Distinguished Professor of International Finance at the Kellogg School of Management. He is also a co-director of the Center for International Macroeconomics at Northwestern University. He received his doctorate in economics from University of Rochester in 1989, and has served in a variety of roles in the non-profit sector. He is a fellow of the Econometric Society, and a research fellow at the Center for Economic and Policy Research. His research primarily focuses around macroeconomics, economic systems, and international finance.
